<GmapID>0x8082d878557e558f:0xaefa16a9c68578b6</GmapID></record></dataset><record>
<Rating>5< /Rating><gmapID>0x8082d878557e558f:0xaefa16a9c68578b6</gmapID>< text>
This place is great. The beers on tap are amazing. They have an app called DigitalPour in which you can see if your favorite beers are still on tap, the price, and how much of the keg is available. The staff are super great and really friendly.

One of the other really cools things about this place, (aside from the ping pong table and giant jenga set in the back), is that you can bring in whatever food you want as they don't have a food license so you're welcome to bring in anything.

This place is great for a casual and chill meetup with friends or an after work beer. I would definitely recommend checking this place out.

Thanks the Chico TapRoom Staff and Owners, you all rock!<//text>

<UserId.>108514700518701630951</UserId.>< user_name>
Tom Mathews</user_name>
<date>1425104333993<//date><rating>5</rating>< Review>
One of the most authentic Indian Cuisine, I have had in ages... A complete nostalgic feel swept past me throughout the entire time over here... If you are craving for some authentic South Indian Cuisine, this the place you should be at... This place might come across to a few to be a bit shabby, but I would say please don't judge the book by it's cover... I recommend this to everyone, if they are interested in experiencing the true south Indian flavors...

We had a plain dosa, paneer keema dosa, chicken biryani, naan and kadai paneer... The biriyani had super cool rice, and well cooked chicken pieces... The Dosa, were just incredible... Crisp with superb sambar and chutney's on the side...

The place has quite a lot of parking space< /Review>

<user_id>100187286467151719613< /user_id><name>Viracocha< /name><Date>1413684793111<//Date><rating>3< /rating>< Text>
Order at counter upfront (10% cash discount only for students)

Chutney etc are self serve so that's good - cocunut, red tomato, chilly garlic, mint and tamarind chutneys (chilly garlic might be spicy so be cautious on how much qty u mix) ...mixed them all and tasted good

Tried idli-vada-masala dosa combo

Dosa with masala bhaji (mashed potato) was good with chutney ..if u don't like soggy dosa due to inside masala bhaji request keeping the bhaji on the side..also bhaji qty might appear less however it was enough (ie perfect qty unless u like eating more)

Vada taste was average

Sambar was good with idli (good thing is they don't serve idli inside sambar, which some ppl may not like)

Good spacious place< /Text>

It‚Äôs still early, but as far as I can tell, two days later I‚Äôm pain free and still happy with my choice.

As for COVID procedures: masks required until you reach the exam room. Plenty of hand sanitizer around. Small staff, cozy office, but I did not feel crowded. A lot of sterilization happened when I left the room. That made me feel good.

Thank you Dr. Glasband and staff!<//Text>

<Name>Brian Vasquez<//Name><UserId.>101876271661184473784< /UserId.>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< response>
None<//response>
<gmapID>0x80c2c639a6f42fcb:0xbd443a1d5068bb52<//gmapID>< Text>
ALWAYS FILLING

1. DETAILS & EXPERIENCE
I don't come often to Beard Papa's, but every time I have, it's always been a delightful experience, with richness enveloped deep inside the pastries, Beard Papa's is a must for all who love cream within their desserts. A major shout-out to Vanessa, who was not only working alone, but handling an entire line of customers, with fast speed, efficient work (Noticed how she did her job in the back), and a great smile. Major credit to where its due.

The mochi's here are really good. I got mango and chocolate. I've tried Mochi in other places, but here it seems to have a good soft taste without it being overly sweet. It's a nice balance and they do a good job here. I also liked the Creme Brulee Tart and watching the process in how its made. It wasn't overly sweet and it hit just the right spot. I tried a strawberry thing which had glazed strawberry cream over it and strawberry cream inside. (Forgive me, I forgot the name of it) Anyways, it wasn't the best, but it wasn't bad either, perhaps just not my taste. Perhaps it could have been better with some fresh strawberries inside of the item, that could have been interesting.

2. SETTING
It's located within a mall, so its always expected to be ventilated. Plenty of seats outside and a few inside.

3. PRICE, QUANTITY, & QUALITY FOR PRICE
$5+
I say 5 because its always nice to leave a tip, but its definitely affordable.

4. SUGGESTIONS
Creme Brulee is nice. Not only does it taste good, but its cool to see the process how its made. Makes it a much more enjoyable experience.

5. FINAL THOUGHTS
None. Beard Papa's has always been good to me. Definitely planning on trying out more items next time I return.</Text>

< Name>
Maryna Varenikava<//Name>
< review>
Labor and Delivery department nurses are wonderful.

I've been anxious while checking-in as my family was not able to stay with me at the hospital due to Covid-19 - kids under 12 years old are not allowed so we agreed that my husband will stay at home with our daughter as we didn't know how soon I will deliver the baby and be discharged.

Ashley was the first (night) nurse I met and she made me feel so comfortable and relaxed, she was very caring, she helped me whenever I needed something and supported me when there've been any doubts.

Natashia and Vick did a great job during the day hours.

And finally, Channel was the nurse who assisted with the baby delivery, she's amazing! She coached me, and cared for me, and inspired me when i had no more power to proceed.

When the baby was born she's been placed skin-to-skin on me and she was checked by the doctors right there, we stayed together for a rather long wonderful time before she was taken to that baby-table for weight check and the shot. Nurses reminded me and took many photos for me to share with the family.

I never felt lonely during my stay at the Labor and Delivery department and received an excellent care. I am very grateful for that to each person whom I met there.

Marie was the night nurse at the Mother and Baby department and I felt at home with her too. She was a great help and so passionate!

I would like to mention how quick and easy was the process of baby vital documents submission, the lady was great at gathering correctly all the information by phone (we have not so simple names and last names, you know :)). By the way, no issues this time - we received them all soon by mail.

The Meal Services were so kind to check with me several times if I really didn't want anything as they 'saw' that I was getting late with the discharge from the hospital.

It was a great experience. Many thanks to everyone involved!< /review>

< review>
If you are going to be sick, well there isn't a much better place to be than here at Kaiser. The hospital and medical offices are top notch. The Doctors, nurses and staff are good. I hope you don't have to come here, and you remain healthy, but if you must come here rest easy and know that they will do their best to help you. If you are family, they work to accommodate you and make you comfortable. The seating is nice, the decor has comforting colors and artwork. There are areas where you can be alone and in peace. Kids are welcome and they often cheer you up just by being themselves There are a couple of pharmacies in the building, so getting medicine is convenient. What is not convenient is parking. You may often drive around looking for a spot. I recommend going across the bridge and parking there and walking back, as you can readily find a spot over there. I hope you don't have to come here, except for routine check ups, colds and flu. It is a highly recommended hospital and medical organization.</review>

<review>Visited them when our little one had a severe asthma attack. There were no many visitors there, and we were accepted immediately. The staff was very careful and professional. They did the checks, and in just 5 minutes we were on a way to the room. The following two nights were a nightmare for me and my wife due to the fact we had this stress situation, but I cannot say anything bad about the staff, doctors or the hospital.

Here are some of my observation. They may sound a bit harsh, but they don't change my overall positive opinion:
1. The staff is constantly rotating. I'd say it happens once a day but may be not. It means that the quality may change depending on who is on duty today. One day it could be just awesome, another day it could be so-so. It never was "bad" for us.
2. The "main" doctors (who are rotating as well) are good. The
"assistant doctors" are not that good/skilled sometimes. There was a case when I had to intervene and begin to give advices. I'm not a doctor at all, but being an engineer I managed to learn the hardware in the room better than the doctor who tried to set it up. I don't tend to think that something bad could happen without me. However, it was a disappointment to see the inability to operate a simple medical device. It was just a single case during the whole stay. Most of the time the staff knew what they are doing.
3. The food for the little patients is acceptable, but nothing special. It wasn't a big issue to us since our little girl had no appetite anyways. However, the picky ones would likely not eat the whole meal.
4. They have a good playing room and a playground. It could be a big relief when the kid has spent a couple of days in the hospital.
5. I had an experience to communicate with their financial department, and the experience was positive. They are friendly and responsive.

Use caution if you have Anthem Blue Cross Insurance.  You will end up with unexpected high bills that you are responsible for.  I was traveling on business and became ill.  I looked up the closest medical facility and drove myself there for care.  The medical care was great maybe even overkill.  I use a competing insurance provider and did not realize that Kaiser and Anthem do not play nice together.  Kaiser did not deduct reasonable and customary charges from my bill and would not when I called to request it from billing.  The ugly part was I didn't even see a bill for 5 months after I was treated.  I ended up with almost $450 out of pocket in expenses that under normal circumstances I would not have had to pay had I used an BlueCross friendly Hospital.  I will not use another Kaiser medical facility by choice unless I have Kaiser medical insurance.

The Bill is paid.  The Doctors get 5 stars the Billing department gets 1 star.  Hence the 3 star rating.</Text>

<date>1538601174780< /date>< Text>
I understand that Kaiser Permante is a low cost industrial medical complex. Their thruput of patients is second to none. If you go to the Santa Clara Center allow 45 extra minutes to find a parking place. It would be wise to schedule your heart transplant, colonoscopy, and flu shot for the same visit. That way you will not have to fight someone for a parking place each time.
I went today to get my second shingles vaccine. It is recommended that it be done between 3 and 6 months from the initial vaccine. Kaiser was out of vaccine. Wasted trip. I was told they will get their order at the end of the month. Check back if you can get through.
Earlier this year I went to the sleep apnea clinic. Sat in a big room with a bunch of people kind of like group therapy. Kaiser found it more efficient to have us talk about our sleep problems with a bunch of other people like I was doing this to myself and could change if I really wanted to.
To be more efficient they gave us these monitors to take home and use at night so that they could determine if we had sleep apnea. Mine was broken and didn‚Äôt work. I called the number on the machine and they told to just bring it back the following morning and they would give me a new one to do the test with. 2 more trips to Kaiser.Never got a diagnosis or a CPAP machine. I would rather die in my sleep.
I think I may bail on Kaiser and spend a little more and go back to Sutter Health. Sometimes it ain‚Äôt all about the money.</Text>

<UserId.>106480518297692699244< /UserId.><user_name>Will Kus</user_name>< Time>
1615224042168</Time>
<Rating>4</Rating>< Text>
Large park, lots of people and activity.  The fields are very active now that outdoor sports are allowed.  There are people who come and mingle their dogs by the Senior Center area.  There is usually parking by the Senior Center parking lot, which is next to La Fogata and also open and has outdoor seating.

There is a large dirt track to walk around, with basketball and tennis courts.  The baseball diamonds are usually full but sometimes you can find one open and 2 or 3 people just practicing on it.  There is also an outdoor gym area.  There is also an indoor basketball gym and swimming pool but I think both are closed right now.  Also the only bathrooms that are open are way on the other side of the park near the childrens playground.

The only reason I give it 4 stars is because there are a lot of dark and sketchy areas of the park once it gets dark. And some parking lots get crowded fast.< /Text>

I thought I had told you about this b4 but  I love this park I used to walk dogs in this park and teach children things about dogs in the park and it's just generally pleasant it has a nice track for those that would like to run a little bit of track of a little running a little walking their shady areas they have a lovely children's area there which is mostly shaded they have a swimming pool on site and dressing rooms inside they have tennis courts you can rent and yet it's not the biggest park in the world but they have really made great use of the space including an outdoor gym. 5< /rating>
< Review>
This is my local park that I love! It has great amenities that most other parks don't have like a track you can run on and an outdoor fitness zone. The outdoor swimming pools are fun too! Wall-ball, tennis, Basketball, soccer, ropes and volleyball are also available outside. You can rent courts or sections of grass for personal tournaments or Bday Parties. This park is also very safe, even at night. However I don't understand why this park has Van Nuys in the name? Its in the middle of Sherman Oaks nowhere near Van Nuys just an FYI.</Review>

<rating>5</rating><user_name>E M R< /user_name><time>1522519381337<//time>< Review>
My kids have been playing rec sports here for years and what we love about it is that they learn great skills at their sports without all the intense stress of some of the private leagues.  The instructors have been very patient and encouraging with newcomers yet they are also able to work with the more advanced players.  Also- when there have been inappropriate parent yelling from sidelines they have have taken care of it very respectfully.  This is a great park that has enriched her my kids athletic abilities. Try it out for yourself!<//Review>

<time>1478487357576</time><rating>3</rating>< text>
This public park had a myriad of facilities that are fairly well equipped. Soccer, baseball, tennis, squash, basketball, weight training (outdoors city provided machines) and a decent gravel running path. The lack of 4 or 5 starts is sure to the fact that the majority of the facilities are a little worn out (soccer, baseball, and indoor basketball are top notch though), but worse still is the vagrancy problem. Though to be fair it's hardly ever an issue. Not the most friendly place to run in the evening due to that issue.</text>

<rating>5</rating>< review>
This is the best park in the Sherman Oaks/Van Nuys Area.  It's huge and has everything.  From 16 tennis courts, to 4 basketball courts, to several baseball diamonds and soccer fields.  It also has the best playground for kids in the area (actually two playgrounds, a playground for toddlers and playground for bigger kids).  The only downside is that there is also a CRAZY kids birthday scene that happens all weekend as well, with very elaborate (invite only) parties being run in one corner of the park.

Kind Friendly Rating: High</review>
